/** 
 * Implementations of this interface provide read and/or write access to the backdrop, the visual layer that is rendered beyond the 3d scene rendered by the WorldRenderer This is generally intended to be the sky, but the theatrical term "backdrop" is used to include anything in the background. On the other hand, the term "background" itself was avoided as it is used in the context of background/foreground processes and threads.
 */
public interface BackdropProvider {
  float getDaylight();
  float getTurbidity();
  float getColorExp();
  float getSunPositionAngle();
  Vector3f getSunDirection(  boolean moonlightFlip);
}
